<div class="hero"><div class="hero-inner">
<div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Sales how-to</div>
<h1 class="hero-h">How to prep for sales calls <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">with Claude.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Most sales reps either spend 90 minutes prepping or skip prep entirely. Both produce worse outcomes than a focused 10-minute Claude-assisted prep. Here is the exact workflow that produces a structured prep brief in under 10 minutes per call.</p>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">The premise</span><h2 class="h2">Why traditional prep is broken</h2>
    <p class="body">The traditional model: rep researches account 30-90 min, opens CRM history 10 min, writes question list 10 min. Total: 50-110 minutes per call. Most reps cannot sustain that across 8 daily calls, so they skip prep entirely.</p>
    <p class="body">The AI-assisted version: rep pastes 3 inputs into a Claude Project, gets back a structured prep brief in 10 minutes. Quality is equal or better. Sustainability is dramatically higher.</p>
    </div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">The 4-step workflow</span><h2 class="h2">How it works</h2>
    <p class="body"><strong>1. Gather inputs (2 min).</strong> CRM activity history, the contacts LinkedIn, the original lead source/email exchange that booked this call.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>2. Run the prep prompt (1 min).</strong> Paste into your Sales Project. Claude returns structured brief.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>3. Skim the brief (3 min).</strong> Verify accuracy. Note the 1-2 unexpected things Claude surfaced.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>4. Plan the call (4 min).</strong> Pick your top 3 discovery questions, your one social proof point, and your one strong next-step ask.</p>
    </div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">The Claude prep prompt</span><h2 class="h2">Use this</h2>
    <p class="body"><pre>I have a call with [PERSON] at [COMPANY] in 30 minutes.

Account activity (from CRM): [PASTE]
Their LinkedIn summary: [PASTE]
What they engaged with that booked this call: [PASTE EMAIL THREAD OR FORM SUBMISSION]

Return a prep brief (max 400 words, I will read in 5 minutes):

1. 2-sentence context summary (who they are, why we are talking)
2. Their likely top 2-3 priorities this quarter (inferred from role, company stage, recent moves)
3. 5 specific discovery questions tailored to their context
4. 2 likely objections and how I would respond
5. The strongest reason for them to take a next step
6. 1-2 things I should NOT say (false assumptions that could be wrong)
7. The 1 most credible social proof to mention

Be specific. Generic discovery questions are useless.</pre></p>
    </div></section>

